        },
        {
            "_id": "qV4pHys0UrAOFtPw",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Warshard Wight Spawn",
            "sort": 800000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A living humanoid slain by a warshard wight's scything blade or claw Strike rises as a spawned wight after [[/br 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}. This spawned wight is under the command of the warshard wight that killed it. It doesn't have drain life or warshard wight spawn and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 2} for as long as it's a spawned wight. If its creator dies, the spawned wight becomes a full-fledged, autonomous warshard wight; it regains its free will, gains drain life and warshard wight spawn, and is no longer clumsy.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
